children.text: There have been incorrect brick ties used to connect the veneer brickwork to the frame, instead of using the appropriate brick ties.
e relevant Australian Standard, AS 3700 Masonry Structures, requires in section 3.4 Ties & Accessories that
‘The type and duty rating of wall ties shall be specified. Where they are designed to connect structural elements, the design strength and stiffness of accessories shall also be specified’

‘The mean tie strength (Ft) of Type A veneer wall ties shall be not less than the values given in Table 3.5. The design strength of Type A cavity wall ties shall be not less than the values given in Table 3.6’ .

As these ties do not have the type and duty rating specified, and clearly do not meet the requirements of the Australian Standards, these sections of brickwork will either need to be demolished and reconstructed using appropriate brick ties, or otherwise the builder will need to have these ties tested in a laboratory to confirm they comply with the provisions of Australian Standard AS 2699.1 Wall ties for masonry construction, and Australian Standard AS 3700 (shown above).
